                    "company": "Adyen",
                    "description": "My main focus at Adyen is working as a Data Visualization Designer. I create static designs for the different reports, dashboards and all other facets that are improved through the visualization of data (such as an organogram). I build almost all my final fully-fledged visualization with d3.js, but I also work with tools such as Sketch, Adobe Illustrator and R for the design and data preparation phase.\n\nSteps that are typically involved in creating a new data visualization or dashboard are:\n\n    \u2022 Get an understanding of the goal by talking to the customer/users\n        \u2022 What questions should the users be able to answers with the dashboard?\n    \u2022 Investigate the data that is needed and that which is available for the dashboard\n    \u2022 Design rough sketches of the dashboard, always try to think om more than 1 way\n    \u2022 Select the best ideas and create a static (or simple browser based) version of the dashboard\n    \u2022 Run your design(s) by the users to get feedback\n    \u2022 Work towards a final design that can then be build either by myself or team members",
