                    "company": "Deloitte",
                    "description": "As a Senior Consultant at Deloitte's service line of Business Intelligence and Analytics I worked as a Data Scientist & Data visualization specialist. \n\nIn the field of Analytics I have experience with customer segmentation, association analysis, text mining and retention modelling in retail, banking, insurance and consumer business. During my time at Deloitte I have become mostly specialized in Customer Analytics\n\nI was responsible for all tasks associated with data manipulation and analytical applications in projects to find insights in client data. My main tasks included:\n    \u2022 Converting business questions into an analytical roadmap of tasks to perform\n    \u2022 Gathering intelligence about data availability and constructing a data model\n    \u2022 Cleaning, enriching and joining client data to prepare it for modelling (R, SAS, SQL)\n    \u2022 Analyzing data using either statistical software or self-written algorithms (R)\n    \u2022 Visualizing results in graphs or custom made interactive designs (R, D3.js, JS, Adobe CC)\n    \u2022 Transforming the insights into strategic next steps\n\nIn the last year at Deloitte I focused on advanced data visualization (not dashboards). Creating custom made visuals of client data or content for publications. I also helped other teams improve on their charts to generate a more lasting impact and make them more effective. For my own work I often use a combination of D3.js (and other JavaScript libraries), R and Illustrator.",
